<span id="freeTextContainer10663243836162711918">Did my 5th re-read of this book yesterday. I used to love it--really, I did.<br/><br/>But things changed. My views have changed, and I can&apos;t let the fact that Derek shagged that housewench as a sub for Sara go. It felt unclean for me, and was so downright disrespectful to women in general. No woman should be used for her body like that. Enough.<br/><br/>And this delineation between pure, naive Sara and the unclean OTHER women? Yeah, that can go to hell. I&apos;m sick of that shit.</span>
  <span id="freeText10663243836162711918" style="display:none">Did my 5th re-read of this book yesterday. I used to love it--really, I did.<br /><br />But things changed. My views have changed, and I can't let the fact that Derek shagged that housewench as a sub for Sara go. It felt unclean for me, and was so downright disrespectful to women in general. No woman should be used for her body like that. Enough.<br /><br />And this delineation between pure, naive Sara and the unclean OTHER women? Yeah, that can go to hell. I'm sick of that shit.</span>
