        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3821981413" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1015335133817516307"><blockquote>
  <b>
    <i>”This isn’t happening at all. You’re just visiting a dream of mine.”<br/>“Am I?” He bent his head, his smiling mouth very close to hers. His breath was warm against her lips. “Then don’t wake up, angel. I’d like to stay awhile.” </i>
  </b>
</blockquote> <br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1612823263ra/30833894.gif' width='480' height='224' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/> <br/><br/>This story starts out with our heroine Sara walking the darks alleys of London all in the purpose of researching her next novel. Ah, what would we do without google in today&apos;s age? While she&apos;s out and about a handsome man is attacked by two hired hands and our b</span>
  <span id="freeText1015335133817516307" style="display:none"><blockquote>
  <b>
    <i>”This isn’t happening at all. You’re just visiting a dream of mine.”<br>“Am I?” He bent his head, his smiling mouth very close to hers. His breath was warm against her lips. “Then don’t wake up, angel. I’d like to stay awhile.” </i>
  </b>
</blockquote> <br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1612823263ra/30833894.gif" width="480" height="224" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br><br>This story starts out with our heroine Sara walking the darks alleys of London all in the purpose of researching her next novel. Ah, what would we do without google in today's age? While she's out and about a handsome man is attacked by two hired hands and our brave, bookish Sara takes a <b>PISTOL </b>out her purse and saves the day. She then takes mystery man to his place which happens to be the biggest and most popular gambling hall in London, <i>Craven's</i>. &amp; yes, mystery man is legendary blackguard and owner of said den of iniquity, Derek Craven. From there to repay her debt he "tolerates" her frequenting his place, interviewing the staff, nothing misses her questions and she slowly imbeds herself at Craven's and the man himself. <br><blockquote>
  <b>
    <i>"Derek had never dreamed that his territory would be so gently and thoroughly invaded—or that his employees would be such willing traitors. Sara Fielding’s mysterious charm had captivated everyone in his club."</i>
  </b>
</blockquote><br>From here we have fallen man trying to do his best to keep her safe from herself &amp; and from him. All while getting all the banter and tension that we love. &lt;3 also they're freaking hilarious<br><br><b>
  <i>“Still carrying the pistol?” he asked, casually amused. <br>“I try to be prepared for any situation.” <br>“Well,” Derek mocked, “the next time things get tight around here, I’ll know who to come to.”</i>
</b><br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1612826819ra/30834023.gif" width="480" height="270" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br>---------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>MR. DEREK CRAVEN 💕♥️💍: what a book <s>boyfriend</s> husband. <br><b>
  <i>"Closed in a small room with these gently-born men, he seemed like a panther keeping company with house cats."</i>
</b><br>Derek is a man who came from nothing and made himself into one of the wealthiest men in London. He's crude, blunt, and all cockney. However for those under his skin and his protection he's kind and generous and you can't help but see all the good in him. So when Sara starts to slowly crawl under his armor he doesn't know what to do because all he sees is his dirty past. <br><b>
  <i>"She belonged with a decent man. A stab of violent jealousy .... caused Derek to scowl."</i>
</b><br> He doesn't do anything in halves and you can see that every time he is on the page. Him being subtly obsessed with her. Swoonnnnn. <br><br>And Sara was such a great heroine. <br><b>
  <i>“A long time ago I learned not to explain things to people. It misleads them into thinking they’re entitled to know everything I do.”</i>
</b><br>Sara is a country girl who lives vicariously through the stories she writes. No one knows how she is since she stays unassuming and reclusive. However, during her time with Craven and his club you can see her flourish into herself. She's pragmatic, observant, and she stands up for herself. And as she stays in his orbit she sees under his burly persona the more she wants to prove that she can make it in his world. <br><b>
  <i>“Not a mouse tonight,” she had whispered with a wondering smile. “You won’t even know me, Mr. Craven.”</i>
</b><br><br><b>TL;DR: </b>I loved this! First read of apparently a lot of people favorite regency author. I am onto another one of her books very soon 😍😍</span>
  <a data-text-id="1015335133817516307" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


