<div id="review_1811417226" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1811417226" />
    <a title="Holly" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7383561-holly"><img alt="Holly" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1374678939p2/7383561.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1811417226?book_show_action=true">Nov 13, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Holly" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Holly" href="/user/show/7383561-holly">Holly</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/6659136-dreaming-of-you">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7383561-holly?shelf=historical-romance">historical-romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7383561-holly?shelf=2018-read">2018-read</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1811417226" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10350189365689467618">Lisa Kleypas is one of my favorite Historical Romance authors, but based on this I am not sure I want to go further back than her Wallflowers series. The writing style is still the same, which I like, but the insta-romance is a downer and there weren&apos;t any &quot;fun&quot; interactions like we later see in her Hathaways series (and I hope to see with West in her book coming out next year, <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/40404706.Devil_s_Daughter__The_Ravenels___5_' title='Devil&apos;s Daughter (The Ravenels, #5) by Lisa Kleypas' rel='nofollow noopener'>Devil&apos;s Daughter</a>). This one also felt a bit slow at times. This was good, but I know this author wrote much better late</span>
  <span id="freeText10350189365689467618" style="display:none">Lisa Kleypas is one of my favorite Historical Romance authors, but based on this I am not sure I want to go further back than her Wallflowers series. The writing style is still the same, which I like, but the insta-romance is a downer and there weren't any "fun" interactions like we later see in her Hathaways series (and I hope to see with West in her book coming out next year, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/40404706.Devil_s_Daughter__The_Ravenels___5_" title="Devil's Daughter (The Ravenels, #5) by Lisa Kleypas" rel="nofollow noopener">Devil's Daughter</a>). This one also felt a bit slow at times. This was good, but I know this author wrote much better later on.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10350189365689467618" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
