<div id="review_1657565189" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1657565189" />
    <a title="Azet" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/42316620-azet"><img alt="Azet" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1627396272p2/42316620.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1657565189?book_show_action=true">Apr 17, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Azet" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Azet" href="/user/show/42316620-azet">Azet</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/42316620-azet?shelf=alpha-hero-macho">alpha-hero-macho</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/42316620-azet?shelf=favourites">favourites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/42316620-azet?shelf=historical-romance">historical-romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/42316620-azet?shelf=love-the-hero-love-interest">love-the-hero-love-interest</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/42316620-azet?shelf=love-the-heroine">love-the-heroine</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/42316620-azet?shelf=badboy-rake-anti-hero">badboy-rake-anti-hero</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/42316620-azet?shelf=romance-genre">romance-genre</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/42316620-azet?shelf=jealous-smitten-possessive-hero">jealous-smitten-possessive-hero</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/42316620-azet?shelf=steamy-erotic">steamy-erotic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/42316620-azet?shelf=by-lisa-kleypas">by-lisa-kleypas</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1657565189" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13149150570117077550">I have wanted to read &quot;Dreaming of You&quot; ever since i read &quot;Then Came You&quot; last year and got to meet the very beloved Anti-hero Derek Craven!(i see that every member in Goodreads are madly awed by this hero)I was so captivated by his dark mysterious character that i wanted to meet the one lady who would bring this rake down his knees.Lisa Kleypas is a marvelous writer who delivered much drama,intrigue,emotions,love,passion that was so smoldering that i simply couldn`t stop reading.I love the stor</span>
  <span id="freeText13149150570117077550" style="display:none">I have wanted to read "Dreaming of You" ever since i read "Then Came You" last year and got to meet the very beloved Anti-hero Derek Craven!(i see that every member in Goodreads are madly awed by this hero)I was so captivated by his dark mysterious character that i wanted to meet the one lady who would bring this rake down his knees.Lisa Kleypas is a marvelous writer who delivered much drama,intrigue,emotions,love,passion that was so smoldering that i simply couldn`t stop reading.I love the story-line,developement of romance and all the characters that brought light to the story.<br /><br />Sara Fielding of Greenwood Corners is a very passionate novelist who one fateless evening saves the life of Derek Craven, the notorious owner of a gambling club and in return he has to let her join into his dark life for her research of the destruction of a gambling life.Despite her innocence i liked how she handled Derek.They both baffled each other since they were so different in natures,but they fall in love with each other against their will,and that was bittersweet to watch!I loved the scene where she masquerade herself as a temptress that resembles her main-character in her written novel,and captures the eyes of everyone in the ball including Derek.Oh that scene made my toes curl!!!<br /><br />Derek Craven is every bit as bad as i thought he would be.Reckless,crude,insolent,manipulative,cold and a rude bastard i just wanted to slap sometimes.He was the defenition of scoundrel.But he was also so irresistibly charming,charismatic and sexy that i wanted to kiss him all along.He was simply gorgeous Alpha of a hero,so bruised and tortured.Sara`s sweetness and pure heart was a temptation his heart couldn`t afford.But he couldn`t stay away from her and i love it when he eventually do ask her to marry him.The way he did it made me laugh.Ah i want a Derek Craven for myself!!!!His love for Sara made my heart melt,he cherishes and respects her so much.I love the eternal love between Derek and Sara,smoldering flames that will never go down.<br /><br />***<br />“For making me want you until I ache with it. For the way I wake at night just to watch you sleeping.” His face was intense and passionate above her, his green eyes harsh in their brightness. “I want you more each time I’m with you. It’s a fever that never leaves me. I can’t be alone without wondering where you are, when I can have you again…”<br />-Derek<br />***<br /><br />We also got appearances by the couple from "The Came You" Alex and Lily and their children.Oh it made me happy watching how they still love each other so much,i missed these two so much!Hope their daughter Nicole will have her own book in the future,she seems to be a promising future heroine! I will say this again,i love you Lisa Kleypas!!!</span>
  <a data-text-id="13149150570117077550" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


